author: wcax.com
title: Deer hunting basics up for discussion next week
text:
CONCORD, N.H. (AP) - The New Hampshire Fish and Game Department is giving a free talk on deer hunting basics.
Whitetail deer are New Hampshire's most sought-after game animal. Last year, hunters took 11,395 deer in the state.
The talk by hunter education instructor Dave Priebe is scheduled for Wednesday at 7 p.m. at department headquarters in Concord.
Other talks coming up are "Hunting Dominant Bucks" on Oct. 14; and "150 Years of Fish and Game History," on Oct. 21.
